<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1903-09-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1903-09-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="535" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d535">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Merry</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">San Jose,
                                        Costa Rica</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1903-09-22"><hi rend="italic">September 22,
                                    1903</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Merry reports that the Salvadorean Congress ratified on the 22d
                            instant the agreement for the settlement of the arbitration of the
                            Salvador Commercial Company’s claim.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>